``The IASB in particular has often been cited as the prime example of a standard setter that is removed from public interference and accountability,77 and although the BCBS has long participated in IASB public consultation rounds, it remains only one among a wide range of commenters, with an assigned status no different from any other participating party (including individual academic scholars).'' (M\"ugge and Perry, 2014, p. 207)
